%S A380855 1,0,0,-1,1,-1,0,-1,2,-1,0,-1,2,-2,1,-1,2,-1,0,-1,2,-2,1,-1,3,-3,1,-1,
%T A380855 3,-4,3,-2,2,-1,0,-1,2,-2,1,-1,3,-3,1,-1,3,-4,3,-2,3,-3,1,-1,3,-4,3,
%U A380855 -2,4,-6,4,-2,4
%N A380855 The unique sequence starting with a(0) = 1, a(1) = 0 and partial sums are 1 followed by the sequence terms themselves repeated in successive blocks a(0..2^k-1) for k >= 0.
%F A380855 a(n) = a(A053645(n)) - a(A053645(n-1)) for n > 1.
%e A380855 The defining partial sums as sequence blocks 0..2^k-1 begin
%e A380855   sums  1,  1,    1, 0,   1, 0, 0, -1, ...
%e A380855             ^     \---/   \---------/
%e A380855   blocks   a(0)  a(0..1)    a(0..3)
%e A380855 The formula results in repeats of terms of the sequence itself in blocks,
%e A380855   n=0..1:    1, 0,
%e A380855   n=2:       0,
%e A380855   n=3..4:   -1, 1,
%e A380855   n=5..8:   -1, 0, -1, 2,
%e A380855   n=9..16:  -1, 0, -1, 2, -2, 1, -1, 2,
%e A380855   n=17..32: -1, 0, -1, 2, -2, 1, -1, 3, -3, 1, -1, 3, -4, 3, -2, 2,
%e A380855 Terms at n=9..15 repeat in the next row at n=17..23 since A053645 in the formula "drops" each latter n in the same way as each former n, and in general successive rows repeat excluding the last term.
%e A380855 Each of these blocks has zero sum.
%e A380855 The cumulative sum of this sequence gives:
%e A380855   1,
%e A380855   1,
%e A380855   1, 0,
%e A380855   1, 0, 0, -1,
%e A380855   1, 0, 0, -1, 1, -1, 0, -1,
%e A380855   1, 0, 0, -1, 1, -1, 0, -1, 2, -1, 0, -1, 2, -2, 1, -1,
%e A380855   1, 0, 0, -1, 1, -1, 0, -1, 2, -1, 0, -1, 2, -2, 1, -1, 2, -1, 0, -1, 2, -2, 1, -1, 3, -3, 1, -1, 3, -4, 3, -2,
%e A380855   ...
%e A380855 These terms are concatenated parts of the original sequence each with length of a power of two.
%e A380855 The original sequence itself can also be written in blocks of length 2^k after ignoring the first two terms:
%e A380855 1, 0, <- ignored
%e A380855   0,
%e A380855   -1, 1,
%e A380855   -1, 0, -1, 2,
%e A380855   -1, 0, -1, 2, -2, 1, -1, 2, <- last value 2 but in further occurrences 3.
%e A380855   -1, 0, -1, 2, -2, 1, -1, 3, -3, 1, -1, 3, -4, 3, -2, 2,
%e A380855   -1, 0, -1, 2, -2, 1, -1, 3, -3, 1, -1, 3, -4, 3, -2, 3, -3, 1, -1, 3, -4, 3, -2, 4, -6, 4, -2, ...
%e A380855 We observe here that this sequence converges to a repeating pattern. It appears that if a block of this pattern appears the first time some of the last values in this block may in some cases not yet agree with further occurrences. Despite of this each of these blocks has zero sum.
%o A380855 (PARI)
%o A380855 vectorA(numiter) = {my(v=[1]); for(k=0, numiter, v=concat(v, v-concat(0, v[1..#v-1]))); v[1+#v/2..#v]}
